41:59.317 --> 42:10.595 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JOHN YANG: Finally tonight: an excerpt from
an interview done by our own Robert MacNeil

42:10.695 --> 42:14.766 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
with the late Fidel Castro.

42:14.866 --> 42:18.035 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Conducted in 1985, MacNeil asks Castro to
describe how the Cuban Missile Crisis began.

42:18.136 --> 42:24.675 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Castro said that after the Bay of Pigs invasion
in 1961, Cuba and the Soviet Union feared

42:24.776 --> 42:27.545 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
additional U.S. invasions into Cuba.

42:27.645 --> 42:35.319 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
FIDEL CASTRO, Cuban President (through translator):
The Soviets had that concern, and we naturally

42:35.420 --> 42:37.955 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
had the same concern.

42:38.055 --> 42:43.060 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
ROBERT MACNEIL: This is after the Bay of Pigs?

42:43.161 --> 42:50.668 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
FIDEL CASTRO (through translator): Yes, after
the Bay of Pigs.

42:50.768 --> 42:54.405 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
They asked us what measures we thought couldoffer Cuba some guarantees.

42:54.505 --> 43:04.582 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
The most sure one was the fact that an aggression
against Cuba mean an aggression against the

43:04.682 --> 43:06.150 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Soviet Union.

43:06.250 --> 43:10.021 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
That was the thesis that we put forth.

43:10.121 --> 43:15.793 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
The concrete idea of the missiles was theirs.

43:15.893 --> 43:28.473 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
I explained it, and we accepted it, but without
any hesitation, because we were being harassed.

43:28.573 --> 43:34.412 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
An invasion had just taken place.

43:34.512 --> 43:36.981 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
The pirate attacks were continuing constantly.

43:37.081 --> 43:42.086 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Constant mention was being made of an invasion
against Cuba.

43:42.186 --> 44:00.705 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
ROBERT MACNEIL: When the crisis was at its
very height, did you personally think, did

44:00.805 --> 44:07.178 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
you believe that nuclear war was a possibility
on one of those days?

44:07.278 --> 44:10.181 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
FIDEL CASTRO (through translator): Yes.

44:10.281 --> 44:13.918 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
Yes, I believed that as a possibility.

44:14.018 --> 44:33.004 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
ROBERT MACNEIL: What did you feel about yourrole in having brought it to

44:33.104 --> 44:34.205 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
&nbsp;
that point?

44:34.305 --> 44:35.606 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
FIDEL CASTRO (through translator): It wasn't
me.

44:35.706 --> 44:45.816 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
It was the United States, the one that led
us to that point.

44:45.917 --> 44:56.227 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
It was the United States that initiated the
blockade, that initiated, organized the invasion,

44:56.327 --> 45:19.717 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
the sabotage, the pirate attacks, the mercenary
regiment, and those that spoke of an invasion

45:19.817 --> 45:24.021 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
against Cuba.

45:24.121 --> 45:26.023 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It was the United States.

45:26.123 --> 45:27.124 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It wasn't us.

45:27.224 --> 45:29.794 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
And I believe that we answered correctly.

45:29.894 --> 45:31.662 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
I have no doubt whatsoever.

45:31.762 --> 45:37.368 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
ROBERT MACNEIL: After Khrushchev decided to
withdraw the missiles, which you protested,

45:37.468 --> 45:45.476 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
what did he say to you, did Nikita Khrushchev?

45:45.576 --> 46:03.260 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Did he say to you, we have made a big mistake,we shouldn't have done this?

46:03.361 --> 46:05.096 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
&nbsp;
What did he say?

46:05.196 --> 46:09.800 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
FIDEL CASTRO (through translator): Look, we
wouldn't have opposed seeking a solution.

46:09.900 --> 46:22.546 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
When the war came very close, then the leaders
of these two big powers became more aware

46:22.647 --> 46:25.249 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
about the danger.

46:25.349 --> 46:26.250 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
They worked.

46:26.350 --> 46:29.920 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
They were able to achieve detente.

46:30.021 --> 46:39.730 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
But, at that time, we were not in conformity.

46:39.830 --> 46:41.532 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We were not pleased.

46:41.632 --> 46:45.970 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Now, then, after 15 years elapsed, it was
proven that they were right, that a war, a

46:46.070 --> 46:55.012 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
nuclear war, was avoided andthat Cuba wasn't invaded.

